comments: This song was originally written for "The Travelling People", an audio documentary originally broadcast on the BBC Home Service as part of the "Radio Ballads" series produced by MacColl, Peggy Seeger and Charles Parker commencing in 1958.  The programs mixed narrative and songs.  "The Travelling People" was the last of the "Radio Ballads" involving MacColl and Seeger, although Parker produced two later "Radio Ballads" with different collaborators.

name: She Moves Through the Fair
comments: Recorded by Ewan MacColl. Performances of this song by Margaret Barry had already been recorded by Peter Kennedy in Dundalk, County Louth, Ireland in 1952 and by Alan Lomax in London in 1953: these recordings were released on the Margaret Barry retrospective album "I Sang Through the Fairs" in 1998 (Rounder 11661 1774 2).
